      "message": "The point I was trying to make is that it might be simpler to do the following:\n1. call MarkUnusedEntriesForGC with expectations.Positive,\n2. call MarkUnusedEntriesForGC with expectations.Negative,\n3. check that no entries have changed,\n\nas opposed to the current:\n1. call MarkUnusedEntriesForGC with expectations.Positive,\n2. check that no entries have changed,\n3. call MarkUnusedEntriesForGC with expectations.Negative,\n4. check that no entries have changed,\n\nas the former does not require a helper function to perform the same assertions twice without repeating code, which leads to a simpler test that reads linearly.",
